Program: Free Thinking
Title: Riba: The Brits Who Built the Modern World
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b03x1p4n
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 12 Jan 2015
Philip Dodd chairs a discussion between Terry Farrell, Norman Foster, Nicholas Grimshaw, Michael and Patty Hopkins and Richard Rogers recorded at the Royal Institute of British Architects. Producer: Laura Thomas Recorded in association with the Open University. First broadcast 12/03/2014.